When "External User Management" is turned on, internal user management is disabled. This means that the options (tabs) for adding and inviting users don't even appear in the Confluence UI.

This is confusing. People cannot figure out why they can't see the user management options, even if they have all the correct permissions.

Suggestion: The user management options should be visible, but greyed out and with an explanation of why they're not available -- in this case, because of external user management.

This issue arises from a comment on the docs:
{quote}
[Per Franck|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/~pfranck]

(using confluence 4.2.8) I seem not to be able to find the "Add User" interface. After navigating Browse > Confluence Admin > Users I see this: (see attached screenshot)
{quote}

And reply:
{quote}
Hallo Per

It looks as if you have "External User Management" turned on. When it's on, internal user management is disabled. To configure external user management, go to Browse > Confluence Admin > Security Configuration.

I hope this solves the problem!

Cheers, Sarah
{quote}

And reply:
{quote}

Per Franck

Yes it did indeed. Many thanks.

 

(suggestion to add a note on the Users page about external user management if enabled, and instead of removing the controls, just disabling them and explain why they are disabled)
{quote}

